        TAKE_A_GANDER_AT_THE_PRIMER_ON_MONSTER                                = 8685,  -- Take a gander at the primer on monster rearing penned by Chacharoon's superior.
        SELECT_A_TOPIC_NONE_A_MESSAGE_TO_CHACHAROON                           = 8686,  -- Select a topic. None. A message to Chacharoon. First things first. Naming. Raising and rearing. Saying goodbye. A message from the boss.
        DEAR_CHACHAROON_I_MAY_HAVE_TAUGHT_YOU_ALL                             = 8687,  -- Dear Chacharoon, I may have taught you all the basics of caring for feral monsters, but you are still a child. I do not expect you to remember everything, so I have jotted down the things I deem most important.
        PLEASE_DO_NOT_TAKE_THIS_THE_WRONG_WAY                                 = 8688,  -- Please do not take this the wrong way, but I do not yet think you are capable of raising multiple beasts at the same time. One should be plenty for now.
        IF_YOU_DECIDE_TO_TAKE_CARE_OF_ANOTHER                                 = 8689,  -- If you decide to take care of another creature, you will have to part ways with the one for which you are currently caring.
        IF_YOU_ARE_TO_DEVELOP_A_BOND_WITH                                     = 8690,  -- If you are to develop a bond with your animal, then it is best that you give it a name. Do not worry about thinking of the perfect name, because you can always change it later.
        REARING_BEASTS_WITH_AN_EMPHASIS_ON_PERSONAL_GROWTH                    = 8691,  -- Rearing beasts with an emphasis on personal growth will cause them to grow up little by little. When they finally do get big, they might just reward you with something for your efforts.
        EMPHASIZING_ENJOYING_THE_MOMENT_LETS_YOUR_CREATURE_LIVE               = 8692,  -- Emphasizing enjoying the moment lets your creature live at its own pace and does wonders for its spirit. However, it will not get any bigger than it already is.
        DO_NOT_FORGET_TO_BOND_PHYSICALLY_WITH_YOUR                            = 8693,  -- Do not forget to bond physically with your creature. Each species has its own likes and dislikes, though, so try interacting with them in many different ways.
        I_WARN_YOU_AGAINST_BEING_TOO_STRICT_WITH                              = 8694,  -- I warn you against being too strict with them, however. If you do too many terrible things to them, they will succumb to darkness and turn on you.
        MOOGLE_MAGIC_OFTEN_WORKS_TO_CALM_THEM_DOWN                            = 8695,  -- Moogle magic often works to calm them down, but on the off chance it doesn't, you will have to put them down with your own hand. See that it does not come to that.
        IDEALLY_YOU_WOULD_CONTINUE_REARING_YOUR_BEASTS_UNTIL                  = 8696,  -- Ideally, you would continue rearing your beasts until they become adults, but this isn't an ideal world.
        IF_YOU_EVER_HAVE_TO_PART_WAYS_WITH                                    = 8697,  -- If you ever have to part ways with one, please send it to me. I shall look after it to the best of my abilities.
        HOWEVER_I_WILL_ALSO_LEAVE_YOU_THE_OPTION                              = 8698,  -- However, I will also leave you the option to put it down. Maybe putting you in that position will teach you the true value of life.
        YOU_PORE_OVER_AT_A_CONGRATULATORY_LETTER_WRITTEN                      = 8699,  -- You pore over at a congratulatory letter written in large, blocky letters. The message details further information about the recent expansion to your Mog Garden.
        CHACHAROON_YOU_VE_COME_QUITE_A_LONG_WAY                               = 8700,  -- Chacharoon, you've come quite a long way in just a short time. The seeds you've sown in your companion's Mog Garden are beginning to bear fruit. Well done!
        WITH_THE_EXTRA_SPACE_YOU_VE_PIONEERED_THERE                           = 8701,  -- With the extra space you've pioneered, there is now room not just for one creature to raise, but a second as well. Work even harder, and the sky's the limit!
        NO_MATTER_HOW_MANY_YOU_SEE_FIT_TO                                     = 8702,  -- No matter how many you see fit to take care of, however, I strongly recommend that you always keep a closer eye on one in particular, if for no other reason than to prevent your herd from stampeding or otherwise running amok.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_BRING_YOUR_CHARGES_TO                                  = 8703,  -- If you wish to bring your charges to the Mog Garden proper, then I must insist that you only let one accompany you while the remainder stays behind in the rearing grounds.
        YOU_VE_GOT_IT_IN_YOU_TO_BECOME                                        = 8704,  -- You've got it in you to become a positively fabulous caretaker, Chacharoon. Heed my advice and you're sure to go far.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_SEE_HOW_THE                                  = 8705,  -- What will you do? Nothing. See how the critter's doing. Interact with the beast. Give the creature a name. Collect items.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_SEE_HOW_THE_2                                = 8706,  -- What will you do? Nothing. See how the critter's doing. Interact with the beast. Give the creature a name. Change focus. Collect items.
        YOU_HAVE_DECIDED_TO_FOCUS_ON_REARING                                  = 8707,  -- You have decided to focus on rearing %.
